      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels so pointless lately. like i was looking at some photos of the deep field nebulae last night and it just hit me... we are literally nothing. just a tiny speck of dust on a rock in a corner of a galaxy that doesn't even know we're here. everything we do, every struggle, every person we love... it's all going to be erased by the heat death of the universe anyway. how can anyone even bother to get out of bed when none of it actually matters?",
