      "content": "i dont know... that sounds like something people just tell themselves so they don't freak out. it feels like a cope. like, why call it \"precious\" just because it's temporary? an ice cube melting isn't \"precious,\" it's just disappearing. \n\neverything requires so much effort. the eating, the working, the maintaining these relationships just to keep a temporary spark going before it inevitably goes out. if the end result is always zero, why is the struggle to get there considered \"meaningful\"? it just feels like we're all just performing a play for an empty theater. don't you think there's something inherently irrational about trying to find purpose in a system that's fundamentally designed to decay?",
